44:08.055 --> 44:11.090
What brings this on?

44:11.125 --> 44:14.660
I have family near Detroit.

44:14.694 --> 44:16.661
And there's a lot of liquor

44:16.696 --> 44:19.196
coming in across the lake
from Canada.

44:19.231 --> 44:21.265
I heard they were
looking for agents.

44:21.299 --> 44:23.300
Only the best men.

44:23.334 --> 44:25.368
I don't know about that.

44:25.403 --> 44:27.670
Hmm.

44:30.140 --> 44:31.640
May I speak freely, sir?

44:31.674 --> 44:33.675
Please do.

44:34.877 --> 44:36.911
I know you don't trust me.

44:36.945 --> 44:40.214
I'm not sure why, but I'm pretty
confident that's the case.

44:40.248 --> 44:43.083
What makes you think that?

44:43.118 --> 44:46.687
The incessant questions,
the dirty looks,

44:46.721 --> 44:50.056
the insinuations about
my religious beliefs.

44:51.658 --> 44:54.693
We've been over the winslow
shooting 50 times, sir.

44:54.727 --> 44:56.494
Because something
doesn't sit right.

44:56.529 --> 44:58.696
But it doesn't make sense.
Why would I want him dead?

44:58.730 --> 45:01.898
Temptati knows no rank,
Agent Sebso.

45:01.933 --> 45:03.900
What's that supposed to mean?

45:09.439 --> 45:12.240
I do notice you're wearing
new wing tips.

45:12.275 --> 45:14.842
They were on discount.
I got them at Driscoll's.

45:17.545 --> 45:19.146
This is what I mean.

45:19.180 --> 45:21.047
I don't like what you're
implying here, sir.

45:21.081 --> 45:24.550
What you like
is none of my concern.

45:24.584 --> 45:26.718
I need men I can trust.

45:26.753 --> 45:28.353
You can trust me, God damn it.

45:28.387 --> 45:31.723
What do I have to do
to convince you?

45:42.067 --> 45:45.336
I baptize thee in the
name of the father...

45:45.370 --> 45:48.071
- The father.
- Yes.

45:48.106 --> 45:50.240
- ...The son...
- The lord.

45:50.274 --> 45:51.874
Yes lord.

45:51.909 --> 45:55.076
- ...And the holy ghost...
- Amen. Hallelujah.

45:55.110 --> 45:58.279
<i>...In the marvelous
expectation of resurrection</i>

45:58.313 --> 46:01.882
<i>and the righteous blessings
of eternal life...</i>

46:01.916 --> 46:03.717
Deacon Cuffy.

46:05.119 --> 46:07.452
Agent van Alden

46:07.487 --> 46:09.553
of the bureau
of internal revenue.

46:09.587 --> 46:11.020
Have you come here

46:11.054 --> 46:12.988
to be accepted into
the arms of Christ?

46:13.023 --> 46:15.991
I have never
left him, Deacon...

46:16.026 --> 46:17.893
Keep going.

46:17.927 --> 46:20.128
...Though I have at times
turned from his love.

46:20.162 --> 46:22.096
You cannot turn from him, sir.

46:22.131 --> 46:24.932
Whatsoever the compass point,
he is there beside you.

46:24.966 --> 46:27.834
- Yes lord.
- I do know that to be so.

46:30.738 --> 46:34.640
But this man does not.

46:36.809 --> 46:39.210
There is a veil
over his eyes, Deacon,

46:39.244 --> 46:42.513
and a darkness in his soul.

46:43.681 --> 46:45.882
Come forward.

46:45.916 --> 46:47.717
No, thank you.

46:47.751 --> 46:50.319
Young sir, come forward.

46:50.353 --> 46:53.889
